<div class="policy-container">
  <h1 class="policy-title">📜 Terms of Service</h1>
  <p class="policy-subtitle">
     <strong>Swarga Dhamam</strong>
  </p>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <h3>Purpose of Service</h3>
    <p>
     Swarga Dhamam exists solely to provide sacred Hindu last-rite services (Antyeshti Sanskaras) with compassion, equality, and devotion.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <h3>Respect & Conduct</h3>
    <p>
     Visitors and families are requested to:

Maintain silence, cleanliness, and decorum

Respect religious sentiments and rituals

Cooperate with staff and volunteers

Any behavior that disturbs the sanctity of the premises is discouraged.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <h3>Use of Facilities</h3>
    <p>
    Facilities are provided for religious and service purposes only

Misuse or damage to property is not permitted

Users are requested to keep the surroundings clean and green
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <h3>Timings & Appointments</h3>
    <p>
     Prior intimation is preferred for smooth arrangements

Emergency services are extended as per availability

Timings may vary based on rituals, weather, or public safety needs
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <h3>Charges & Payments</h3>
    <p>
   Charges, if applicable, are nominal and transparent

Payments should be made only to authorized representatives

Financial assistance may be provided to needy families upon request
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <h3>Religious Practices</h3>
    <p>
     Rituals are performed according to Hindu traditions

Families may bring their own Purohit

Swarga Dhamam is not responsible for personal ritual variations
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <h3>Privacy & Dignity</h3>
    <p>
      Personal information and rituals are treated with strict confidentiality

Photography or videography is not allowed without permission

The dignity of the departed and the family is always respected
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <h3>Safety & Liability</h3>
    <p>
      Visitors are requested to follow safety instructions

Management is not responsible for loss of personal belongings

Children and elderly visitors should be accompanied carefully
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <h3>
Service Limitations</h3>
    <p>
    While every effort is made to support families:

Services may be affected by natural, legal, or operational constraints

Management reserves the right to regulate services when required
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <h3>Amendments</h3>
    <p>
    These Terms of Service may be updated from time to time to reflect:

Legal requirements

Operational improvements

Community welfare needs

Updated terms will be displayed on the website or premises
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <h3>Governing Values</h3>
    <p>
      All services are guided by:
🕉️ Dharma | Seva | Equality | Compassion

🙏 “In service to the departed, we walk together with faith, respect, and responsibility”
    </p>
  </div>

 
</div>
